Heat the oil in a pan and gently fry the potato cubes for 5-7 minutes, until golden-brown. Add the white wine to the pan and boil until the liquid has reduced by half.Pour in the stock, tomato and cream and bring to simmering point.Gently place the fish pieces into the pan and poach for about two minutes, or until cooked through. Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Gently stir in the chopped chives, taking care not to break up the fish.Pour into a serving bowl and serve.